(324, 1, '2015-12-01 14:16:43', '2015-12-01 05:16:43', '<!-- タイトルここから -->\r\n<div class="detail_tittle">Google Map</div>\r\n<!-- タイトルここまで -->\r\n<!-- コンテンツここから -->\r\n<div class="detail_text">\r\n<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=zLqLT65JvsG4.kbnnvweGOmv0" width="100%" height="400"></iframe>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- コンテンツここまで -->\r\n<!-- タイトルここから -->\r\n<div class="detail_tittle">\r\nAccess Map from Station\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- タイトルここまで -->\r\n\r\n<!-- コンテンツここから -->\r\n<div class="detail_text">\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/ORIGAMI_map_en.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/ORIGAMI_map_en-273x300.jpg" alt="ORIGAMI_map_9.17" width="273" height="300" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-566" /></a>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- コンテンツここまで -->\r\n\r\n<!-- タイトルここから -->\r\n<div class="detail_tittle">\r\nFrom Metro Ginza Line\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- タイトルここまで -->\r\n\r\n<!-- コンテンツここから -->\r\n<div class="detail_text">\r\n1. Please take exit No.1 from Asakusa Station and turn right for approximately 1 minutes.\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline1-thumb-250x187-9869.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline1-thumb-250x187-9869.jpg" alt="Origami_Ginzaline1-thumb-250x187-9869" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-569" /></a>\r\n\r\n2. Turn left where you will find a shopping street and red gate on your left side.\r\n(Shopping street is called ''Nakamise street, Red gate is the gate of Dempoin street)\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline2.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline2-300x225.jpg" alt="Origami_Ginzaline2" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-570" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline3.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline3-300x225.jpg" alt="Origami_Ginzaline3" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-571" /></a>\r\n\r\n3. Turn right at the 1st corner and go straight the narrow street where before shopping street. Continue straight for approximately 3 minutes. You will pass a left side of Sensoji temple at the time.\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline4.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline4-300x225.jpg" alt="Origami_Ginzaline4" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-567" /></a>\r\n\r\n4.  Cross at the cross walk towards Khoaosan Tokyo Origami''s sign.\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline5.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Origami_Ginzaline5-300x225.jpg" alt="Origami_Ginzaline5" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-568" /></a>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- コンテンツここまで -->\r\n\r\n<!-- タイトルここから -->\r\n<div class="detail_tittle">\r\nFrom Toei Asakusa Line\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- タイトルここまで -->\r\n\r\n<!-- コンテンツここから -->\r\n<div class="detail_text">\r\n1. Please take exit ''A2b'' from Asakusa Station via elevator. Cross at the cross walk towards the ''Family Mart'' store directly opposite.\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine1.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine1-300x225.jpg" alt="AsakusaLine1" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-572" /></a>\r\n\r\n2. Turn right and go straight towards ''Kaminarimon'' (large red gate with big Japanese lantern)\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine2.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine2-300x225.jpg" alt="AsakusaLine2" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-573" /></a>\r\n\r\n3. Go straight at narrow road on the right next to the Kaminarimon gate. You will see a Sensoji temple when you walked approximately 3 minutes.\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine3.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine3-300x225.jpg" alt="AsakusaLine3" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-574" /></a>\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine4.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine4-300x225.jpg" alt="AsakusaLine4" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-575" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine5.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine5-300x225.jpg" alt="AsakusaLine5" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-576" /></a>\r\n\r\n4. Continue straight  at  left side of Sensoji temple.  Cross at the cross walk towards Khoaosan Tokyo Origami''s sign.\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine6.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine6-300x225.jpg" alt="AsakusaLine6" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-577" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine7.jpg"><img src="http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AsakusaLine7-300x225.jpg" alt="AsakusaLine7" width="300" height="225" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-578" /></a>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- コンテンツここまで -->', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '324-2', '', '', '2016-01-15 17:45:34', '2016-01-15 08:45:34', '', 142, 'http://khaosan-test.sakura.ne.jp/?post_type=access&#038;p=324', 0, 'access', '', 0),
